SIMPLE: mobile
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mobile
<hw>Mo"bile</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>mobilis</ets>, for <ets>movibilis</ets>, fr. <ets>movere</ets> to
move: cf. F. <ets>mobile</ets>. See <er>Move</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Capable of being moved; not fixed in place or condition;
movable.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Fixed or else <xex>mobile</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Skelton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Characterized by an extreme degree of fluidity;
moving or flowing with great freedom; <as>as, benzine and mercury are
<ex>mobile</ex> liquids; -- opposed to <ex>viscous</ex>,
<ex>viscoidal</ex>, or <ex>oily</ex>.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Easily moved in feeling, purpose, or direction;
excitable; changeable; fickle.</def> <rj><au>Testament of
Love.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The quick and <qex>mobile</qex> curiosity of her disposition.</q>
<rj><qau>Hawthorne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>Changing in appearance and expression under the
influence of the mind; <as>as, <ex>mobile</ex> features</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>Capable of being moved,
aroused, or excited; capable of spontaneous movement.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>6.</sn> <def>Capable of moving readily, or moving frequenty from
place to place; <as>as, a <ex>mobile</ex> work force</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>7.</sn> <def>Having motor vehicles to permit movement from place
to place; <as>as, a <ex>mobile</ex> library; a <ex>mobile</ex>
hospital</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mobile</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Mobile
<hw>Mo"bile</hw> <pr>(m⟦omac⟧"b⟦icr⟧l; L. m⟦ocr⟧b"⟦icr⟧*l⟦emac⟧)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>mobile vulgus</ets>. See <er>Mobile</er>,
<pos>a.</pos>, and cf. 3d <er>Mob</er>.]</ety> <def>The mob; the
populace.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧The unthinking
<xex>mobile</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>South.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mobile</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Mobile
<hw>Mo"bile</hw> <pr>(m⟦omac⟧"b⟦emac⟧l`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>a form
of sculpture having several sheets or rods of a stiff material attached
to each other by thin wire or twine in a balanced and artfully arranged
tree configuration, with the topmost member suspended in air from a
support so that the parts may move independently when set in motion by a
current of air.</def> ⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>mobilise</ent>⟦br⟧
